I remember when...<br>
<br>
- Magician pets didn't have spells (especially earth!)<br>
- Magicians had no pet heals.<br>
- Damage shields lasted for hours if cast on a pet.<br>
- My first sight of a Butcherblock sunset....awe inspiring.<br>
- D'Vinn to zone!<br>
- Spending a few quite hours fishing on the shores of Lake Rathe.<br>
- I spent 2 days camping a Dragoon Dirk.<br>
- There are 87 players in South Karana.<br>
- The most common shout in Greater Faydark was &quot;Has anybody seen my corpse?&quot;<br>
- Nobody understood what enchanters could do and they couldn't get groups.<br>
- The thrill of my first Giant &amp; Griffon revenge kills.<br>
- You could bind anywhere (ok you can still do this on blue servers but it's been years since I last played on one).<br>
- Taking almost a month to get out of level 30 and two months to get out of level 35.<br>
- Accidentally nuking another player or NPC while standing around outside the bank practicing spells...<br>
- Kedge Keep wasn't itemised.<br>
- You could meet new friends while hanging out waiting for the boat. I miss not having to use boats. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kroviksar>Kroviksar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/18/03 12:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4757.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Old School EQ players..</span><hr size=1> We too remember Morrigu, Redhand of the Empire!<br>
<br>
Also:<br>
<br>
Dreaming of the day when we could actually be in on a roll for the Items of Unrest, the Dwarven Work Boots and others.<br>
<br>
The mere sound of a Hag casting meant instant death<br>
<br>
Knowing that Neriak was the most artistically beautiful town in all Norrath<br>
<br>
That damn thousand year run up the ramp into HH Keep from EK. <br>
<br>
Meeting a lion or giffon 1/2 way up that damn ramp from HH Keep and having to run all the way back down to avoid death.<br>
<br>
Seeing the Paineel enterence before it was active and saying &quot; I am not going near that scary looking place&quot;!<br>
<br>
Looking for the place that sells the tickets to get on the boat from Freeport to Faydark, and hoping I had enough money to buy one.<br>
<br>
Bracers of Battle in Crushbone were rare and worth a fortune.<br>
<br>
Jumping out of my skin when I turned the corner for the first time in Neriak 3rd Gate and ran into the ghouls in the Necro guild.<br>
<br>
Discovering the &quot;Secret&quot; enterence to the upper guard walkways in Felwithe ( Behind General Jheel)<br>
<br>
Getting lost in Rivervale<br>
<br>
Seeing the wooden bridge in NK and thinking, &quot;Thats so cool looking&quot;.<br>
<br>
Getting a big group together to do cube quest in Quynos Sewers for the uber +3 STR Earring (and getting lost down there).<br>
<br>
Human Monks were all there was.<br>
<br>
There were many Trolls, because regen was worth the uglyness.<br>
<br>
100pp for a port to Toxx was a bargin.<br>
<br>
Dying in too far in befallen meant the chance to reroll, because you just lost any hope of getting your corpse back.<br>
<br>
Could make a mule to kill fish in Quynos, then loot fish off corpse to avoid faction hit for Stein quest.<br>
<br>
